Pretty good work, a very enjoyable work with a lot of charm. Really enjoyable but there are some major gripes and questions I had, firstly, why was the maid chapter thrown in with little to no regard for the rest of the story, it's not a bad comic, just out of place. Secondly, a replacement cost of 100,000 dollars on a van is a little steep, and then saying they only did that so they could learn a punishment, it threw the story out the window and made the experience retroactively worse off.
Fapability: 7.5/10, nice looking characters with some good ahegao faces
Story: 3/10, was pretty solid when there was an air of mystery about why they sold themselves but once it was found out it tanked the rating from what would of been at least a 6
Overall enjoyability: 7/10, good if you just want to get the deed done, but if you are looking for a story to rival god himself like I am, look somewhere else.
